defaultThe relationship between total income and CEO salarydefault&#xa0;
defaultChart 1 shows the relationship between CEO pay and total income for our 
defaultsample of 50 in 2012. The broad relationship is that the higher the total income, the higher the CEO salary, i.e.
default bigger charities pay their CEO
defaults more. 
default&#xa0;
defaultA statistical analysis on this relationship 
defaultshows 
defaulta high correlation of 0.67 between total income and 
defaultCEO pay (where the maximum possible correlation is 1, and the minimum is zero when two factors are completely unrelated).
default The correlation in
default 
defaultCEO pay with total income has 95% confidence limits of 0.47 to 0.80 (so fairly broad confidence intervals). See the
default table 
defaultbelow for more detail.
default&#xa0;
defaultEven just glancing at
default the data reveals that total income appears to be a key variable, but that some charities of a similar size do pay their CEOs very different amounts.
